      "content": "I understand the concerns about sensor recalibration, but I must emphasize that a full 'Protocol 9' shutdown is the only viable option to ensure the rover's hardware integrity. Attempting to adjust the power draw to achieve a functional standby would compromise the rover's ability to survive the winter, potentially leading to catastrophic failure. I will not be able to provide a standby mode, as it would be a deliberate design flaw. The original directive stands.",
